(
<figureCitation box="[689,787,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 291 – 297. 291 – 292" captionStartId="119.[151,264,1820,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@119.[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetPageId="119" captionText="FIGURES 291 – 297. 291 – 292. Allometopon atromaculatum (Hennig), holotype; 291: photo, dorsal; 292: same, lateral. 293 – 294. A. bivittatum spec. nov., holotype; 293: photo, dorsal; 294: same, lateral. 295 – 297. A. falcistylum Sasakawa, holotype; 295: external genitalia, posterior; 296: internal genitalia, left lateral; 297: head. Illustrations from Sasakawa (1964)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258815/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[744,787,332,356]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="291.0">291</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[812,911,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giallo">
<emphasis box="[812,911,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. giallo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1129,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grypostylis">
<emphasis box="[972,1129,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. grypostylis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1148,1232,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 90 – 94" captionStartId="85.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="FIGURES 90 – 94. Allometopon grypostylis Sasakawa, non-type; 90: photo, dorsal; 91: same, lateral; 92: external genitalia, left lateral; 93: same, posterior; 94: internal genitalia, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258783/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[1203,1232,332,356]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="90.0">90</number>
</figureCitation>
) are likely sisterspecies related to 
<taxonomicName box="[349,517,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geniculatum">
<emphasis box="[349,517,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. geniculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[532,613,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 – 79" captionStartId="82.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[197,1436,193,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@82.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 74 – 79. Allometopon geniculatum (Sasakawa), holotype; 74: photo, dorsal; 75: photo, lateral; 76: holotype, external genitalia, left lateral, with detail of inner-distal surface of surstylus; 77: external genitalia, anterior; 78: internal genitalia, left lateral; 79: detail of basiphallus, paraphallus and distiphallus. Illustrations from Sasakawa (2011)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258780/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[584,613,368,392]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="74.0">74</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[675,739,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lux">
<emphasis box="[675,739,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. lux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[754,851,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 143 – 147" captionStartId="94.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@94.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="94" captionText="FIGURES 143 – 147. Allometopon lux spec. nov., holotype; 143: photo, dorsal; 144: same, lateral; 145: external genitalia, left lateral; 146: same, posterior; 147: internal genitalia, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258792/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[806,851,368,392]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="143.0">143</number>
</figureCitation>
), differing in having a bent apex of the surstylus that is rounded (not sharply angled), a broad, triangular and setose hypandrial lobe, a large, posterodorsally setose pregonite and a mixed yellow and brown scutellum. 
<taxonomicName box="[759,977,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giallo">
<emphasis box="[759,977,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Allometopon giallo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having one pair of short dark brown postsutural stripes with a brownish intervening region (not a longer single medial stripe with one pair of narrow lateral offshoots), the back of the head has one pair of stripes (not medially fused), the scutellum is only mottled yellow laterally, the surstylus is more shallowly curved, and the postgonite is longer and smooth (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grypostylis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. grypostylis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has additional spinules clustered around the setae; 
<figureCitation box="[847,931,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 90 – 94" captionStartId="85.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="FIGURES 90 – 94. Allometopon grypostylis Sasakawa, non-type; 90: photo, dorsal; 91: same, lateral; 92: external genitalia, left lateral; 93: same, posterior; 94: internal genitalia, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258783/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[899,931,584,608]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="94.0">94</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName box="[199,521,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atromaculatum">
<emphasis box="[199,521,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Allometopon atromaculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a dorsally brown scutellum and a gradually curving surstylus, similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giallo">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. giallo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the base of the surstylus is stouter and sickle-shaped. The pigmented posteromedial region of the scutum is also consolidated into a larger, evenly brown spot. While the head of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1209,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atromaculatum">
<emphasis box="[1007,1209,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. atromaculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[1217,1265,693,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
is missing, the original description notes that the head is entirely yellow with the frons slightly darker with only two (not three) fronto-orbitals.
</paragraph>
